[[Image:Narrenturm Vienna June 2006 577.jpg|thumb|The ''Narrenturm'' in [[Vienna]] (translates to fools' tower) was the first specialised building to lodge mentally ill patients. It was built in 1784. It is a [[museum]] of medical history today.]]
A '''psychiatric hospital''' is a place where [[mental illness|mentally ill]] people are kept until [[Medical doctor|doctors]] are ready to place them into [[halfway house]]s, where they are slowly released into [[society]]. Group homes are open to people when they are released from a psychiatric hospital.

